source.name: Trees in the Public Right of Way
source.description: SDOT standards include the preservation or planting of trees as an integral part of proposals for improvements in the street right-of-way. Selected, installed and protected to provide optimum functional and environmental benefits, trees are required elements of street right-of-way infrastructure to be maintained and preserved for public benefit.
